@article{13020431720180401,
 abstract  = "Objective To study the relationship between serum homocysteine (HCY) and lipid levels and osteopenia in elderly women. Methods We collected data of 126 elderly female patients of our hospital from September 2016 to March 2017. According to the results of dual energy X-ray BMD examination, subjects were divided into normal bone mass group (n=41), osteopenia group (n=43) and osteoporosis group (n=42). Age, menopausal age, time since menopause, height and weight were recorded, and the levels of blood calcium (Ca), phosphorus (P), alkaline phosphatase (ALP), triglycerides (TG), low density lipoprotein cholesterol (LDLC) and high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDLC) were measured. HCY was measured using enzyme linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA). Results The levels of serum HCY and LDL-C in the osteoporosis group were higher than those in the osteopenia group and normal bone mass group, and there were significant differences between the osteoporosis group and the normal bone mass group in",
